<font color="#FF0000">WHO SHOULD HAVE PROTESTED</font><br>
<tt>Fri May  2  1:18:54 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
May 1969 I grew up near Kent State U. and on the day the four students were killed by the national guard everyone took notice because it was on national tv and all who saw the murder of those poor college kids were outraged...but wait VietNam came into our homes on the tv and our poor kids who should of been in college were  getting killed every day but I heard no cries of outrage for them...that is what was wrong with the war protest the wrong people were protesting! When kids protest nobody really pays any atention because they (the estabishment of the time) think these kids don't know what war is all about and when the GI's protest they called them cowards and that they should be ashamed of them selves. But why didn' &quot;they&quot; support the kids that did know what war was about and were brave enough to face the horrors of death that they had to deal with at such a young age. Maybe thats why I took the oppertunity during Desert Storm to activly support our troops as part of the &quot;They&quot; of now I was determined though not to let it turn into another VietNam.<br>

